<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Erudin is Asshole Central...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Dreol">Dreol</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:28 p.m. 22/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Erudin is Asshole Central...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1637" TARGET=_self>Erudin is Asshole Central...</A> (Garbonzo)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> ...I enjoyed my Erudite Necro in beta, so I hoped to continue

<BR>&gt; with one in retail, and hoped to spice it up by playing on
<BR>&gt; Rallos Zek.
<P>&gt; I picked the wrong place to start as a tentative PvP player, let
<BR>&gt; me assure you.
<P>&gt; Partly I blame this on Verant. Tox Forest and Kerra Ridge were
<BR>&gt; mostly ignored in beta by the Dev Team, and thus are laden with
<BR>&gt; safe zones and exploits galore. Naturally, the assholes
<BR>&gt; gravitated to these areas, and quickly outlevelled others (and I
<BR>&gt; know Tox and Kerra Ridge like the back of my hand, know all the
<BR>&gt; exploits there, I found and /bugged most of them back in Phase
<BR>&gt; ONE) then proceed to band together to make life hell for every
<BR>&gt; other Erudite.
<P>&gt; Anyhow, I'm abandoning my 6th level Necromancer (I was 7th, but
<BR>&gt; since Verant now makes Erudite Necros worship the Faceless AND
<BR>&gt; the Qeynos sewer entrance from the docks is broken, you cannot
<BR>&gt; get through til 8th with invis and I was KOS to the guards) and
<BR>&gt; starting over in another area.
<P>&gt; I started in Erudin with 3 friends; all three have abandoned
<BR>&gt; Rallos Zek, disgusted with the asshole factor that seems to
<BR>&gt; center around Erudin.
<P>&gt; I've heard it isn't like this in other cities. I've heard
<BR>&gt; in-race killing is a rare thing, save for guild wars. I hope
<BR>&gt; this is the case, otherwise all the undecideds are gonna abandon
<BR>&gt; PvP in EQ, and Rallos Zek will likely be unviable.
<P>I don't know but I play Erudin on Zek all the time and have not had much in-race PK (except between the Necros as they are hated by the other Erudites) There have been a few times however, here as well as other places, when a random PK here or there happens. I agree, it is a more dangerous place than most, fearing those outcast necros, but it's a lot better than those Human cities...
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
